Help on skill:  The art of bushido
Usage duration: automatic
Skill type:     special
Gi - Rectitude
Yuu - Courage
Jin - Benevolence
Rei - Respect
Shin - Honesty
Yo - Honor
Chuu - Loyalty
Bushido is the tradition of the Samurai, the ethical and moral
pinnacle carried through the ages from each Samurai Warrior to their
eldest proven son. It is the very essence of the Way, and to neglect it
is to forfeit all privilege and status of the Samurai. Bushido can not be
taught, it is only observed and learned through faithful and diligent
adherence to its virtues. This skill does not teach the Art of Bushido,
as each Samurai to reach the status of Samurai Shogunate is brought up to
this tradition from the cradle. Instead, this Art teaches the Samurai
Shogunate on how to display their virtue and adherence to the traditions
to the younger Samurais. As a result, each young Samurai fortunate enough
to join the party of a Samurai Shogunate shall learn from his experience,
gaining mastery in the Samurai's special skills considerably faster.
