Help on skill:     Golden spear
Usage duration:    random
Fatigue:           low
Skill type:        attack
Affecting stat(s): wisdom, charisma and constitution
The Golden Company has vast knowledge about protective invocations that
rival similar magics used by the guild of Abjurers. What the Company does
not possess however, are abilities that would create persistent and potent
vulnerabilities in their targets. In trying to solve this conundrum, one
of the most inventive invoker found out that should the target be holding
a golden conduit, the transference of stellar damage into its frame would
be that much easier. It is, however, often folly to try and ask possible
foes if they would be so kind as to hold on to a conduit while doing
combat.
And so, the members of the Golden Company fashioned a skill that allows
an invoker to quickly fashion a conductive golden spear out of coins
they carry and hurl that projectile against the target, hoping that
it embeds itself deep enough so that it can do its job regardless of how
the target might feel about it. As the conjuration is very volatile, and
often great energies are transfered through the conduit, it will only
last a short while until it disappears altogether.
